of life. It covers the ability of the newborn to see and hear their parents, their natural disposition toward getting to know caregivers, and the growth of love and attachment between parent and baby. It explores the changing mental abilities and social skills in the first and second years, and tells readers how they can observe these stages in children. At a time when parents are increasingly beset by contradictory advice about infant care, many will find it useful to have a sensible and caring book that presents the latest information on understanding the behavior of babies. Parenting can then become the emotionally fulfilling and intellectually stimulating responsibility it should be.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aChild Development. 0aChild Psychology. 0aChild development. 0aChild psychology. 0aInfant psychology. 0aKinderen. 0aKinderpsychologie. 0aOmgeving. 0aOntwikkeling (psychologie). 0aOntwikkelingspsychologie. 0aPsychologie. 0aZuigelingen. 4aChild Development -- popular works. 4aChild Psychology -- popular works. 4aChild rearing. 4aInfant psychology. 4aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Complete eBook Packagez9783110353488oZDB-23-HCO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP e-dition: Social Science eBook Packagez9783110353556oZDB-23-HCI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999z97831104422120 cprintz978067442962840uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.978067442964240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674429642423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674429642/original  a978-3-11-044221-2  HUP eBook Package Archive 1893-1999c1893d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_E